           SHORT="jMax is the java version of Max/MSP"
cat << EOF
jMax is a visual programming environment for building
interactive musical and multimedia applications. 


jMax is a new implementation of the MAX software written
originally by Miller Puckette at Ircam. The name MAX is an
homage to Max Matthews, one of the fathers of computer music. 
EOF
